# =============================================================================
#  apex-agents-bench .env  ---  copy to .env and fill in the keys you actually
#  use. Never commit .env. The .gitignore at repo root enforces this.
# =============================================================================

# --- Generation (test-model providers) --------------------------------------
# Set the key(s) for whichever provider(s) host the model(s) you want to test.
# You only need keys for providers you actually use.

# OpenAI -- required for gpt-5.5-* agent profiles AND for the judge (gpt-5.5).
# IMPORTANT: no leading/trailing whitespace around the `=`. python-dotenv
# will include any spaces in the value, which silently invalidates the key.
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...

# xAI -- required for grok-4.3-* agent profiles.
XAI_API_KEY=xai-...

# DeepSeek -- required for the deepseek-v4-pro-max agent profile.
DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=sk-...

# Anthropic direct API -- NOT used by this project. Claude profiles run via
# AWS Bedrock and are deferred until the same Bedrock plumbing lands in
# apex-bench. Leave commented out unless you explicitly add a Claude profile.
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...

# Google -- NOT used. The project judge is gpt-5.5, not Gemini. The vendored
# Archipelago example defaults to gemini/gemini-2.5-flash; we override.
# GOOGLE_API_KEY=...

# --- AWS Bedrock (for claude-* profiles, currently deferred) ----------------
# Mirror of apex-bench. Not needed if you only run gpt-5.5-*, grok-4.3-*,
# or deepseek-v4-pro-max.
# AWS_REGION=us-east-1
# AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=AKIA...
# AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=...

# --- HuggingFace (dataset fetch) --------------------------------------------
# REQUIRED. The mercor/apex-agents dataset is gated; HF login is required to
# accept the eval-only terms before the first download. After you accept the
# terms, paste the read-scoped token here.
HF_TOKEN=hf_...

# --- Document extraction (Reducto) ------------------------------------------
# Reducto is the vendor grading runner's high-fidelity document extractor: it
# turns the agent's output files (PDF / spreadsheet / slides / docs) into text +
# rendered images for the judge LLM to read. Without it the grader falls back to
# a local extractor that handles .xlsx/.pptx/.docx/.csv text only -- it has NO
# PDF support and renders xlsx charts only if LibreOffice is installed, so any
# task whose answer lives in a PDF or chart would be graded blind. Set this so
# grading sees every artifact. (MERCOR_DELIVERY_API_KEY, if you have it, takes
# precedence over Reducto; either one enables full document extraction.)
# REDUCTO_API_KEY=...

# --- Azure OpenAI (optional; only used with the `--azure` flag) --------------
# When you run with `--azure`, every gpt-5.5 call (agent profile + judge +
# DC-RS synthesizer + TRACE reflector/curator) is routed to your Azure
# deployment instead of OpenAI. Non-gpt-5.5 models (grok, deepseek) are
# unaffected, and embeddings ALWAYS stay on OPENAI_API_KEY. We route via
# LiteLLM's openai/ provider against the AI-Foundry OpenAI-compatible
# /openai/v1 surface (the classic azure/ deployments path 404s on a Foundry
# resource). Uncomment and fill when using --azure:
# AZURE_API_KEY=
# AZURE_API_BASE=https://<your-resource>.services.ai.azure.com/openai/v1   # MUST end in /openai/v1 (no /responses)
# AZURE_GPT55_DEPLOYMENT_NAME=gpt-5.5           # the EXACT deployment name in Azure AI Foundry (default: gpt-5.5)
# AZURE_API_VERSION=2025-07-01-preview          # OPTIONAL / unused by the /openai/v1 path; kept for reference only
